   "source": [
    "2. Identifying Features and Labels\n",
    "\n",
    "In Machine Learning:\n",
    "\n",
    "Features (Input variables) → Independent variables used to make predictions.\n",
    "Labels (Target variable) → Output we want to predict.\n",
    "✔ Feature:\n",
    "\n",
    "Study Hours\n",
    "\n",
    "✔ Label:\n",
    "\n",
    "Marks\n",
    "\n",
    "Here, Study Hours is the input given to the model, and Marks is the output predicted."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "b1a01725-3874-4e2f-ac0d-cc07c61d3217",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "3. Type of Machine Learning Problem\n",
    "\n",
    "Since the output (Marks) is a continuous numerical value, this is a:\n",
    "\n",
    "Supervised Learning – Regression Problem"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "b6279920-1e6a-4ee7-a47d-e91a5b48a49f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "4. Relationship Between Study Hours and Marks\n",
    "\n",
    "From the dataset, we observe:\n",
    "\n",
    "As study hours increase, marks also increase.\n",
    "The relationship appears to be positive and approximately linear.\n",
    "There is a direct proportional trend between input and output.\n",
    "\n",
    "This indicates a positive linear relationship between study time and academic performance."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "e5dfaf1c-e26e-4ad2-adfe-b4d6a2c8cd16",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "5. Prediction Concept\n",
    "\n",
    "Using a simple Linear Regression model, we can predict marks for any given number of study hours.\n",
    "\n",
    "For example:\n",
    "\n",
    "If a student studies 9 hours, the predicted marks would likely be higher than 85.\n",
    "If a student studies only 1 hour, marks remain comparatively low.\n",
    "\n",
    "The model learns the pattern:\n",
    "\n",
    "More study hours → Higher marks"
   ]
  },
